Aurora Labs Ltd (ASX:A3D) is an Australian based company specialising in the development of 3D metal printers, printer software and the supply of associated consumable materials.
We are at the forefront of metal 3D printing technology, with several technologies under development including some of the most affordable metal printers available and revolutionary industrial grade, high speed, large format 3D metal printers that can be used for large-scale industrial manufacturing on a cost effective basis.

We are at the forefront of metal 3D printing technology. We produce the S-Titanium Pro, one of the most versatile and affordable, high quality metal printers available. We are also developing revolutionary industrial grade, high speed, large format 3D metal printers, powder manufacturing and control software that can be used for large-scale industrial manufacturing on a cost-effective basis.
A TEAM OF FREE THINKERS

Our outstanding team is built of inspired Materials Scientists and Surface Engineering specialists, Computer Scientists, Mathematicians and Physicists, we.re driven by the urge to create new things in new ways to meet extraordinary technical challenges.

Mission:

Aurora Labs was created to make 3D metal printing accessible for developers, researchers and creators as well as move 3D printing into high volume manufacturing.

Vision:

We believe weÕre on the cusp of another manufacturing revolution Ð one that takes 3D printing to new heights. We have developed the ability to print multiple metals at the same time, the most affordable metal printers available in their class and are developing what would be the fastest and largest print envelope 3D metal printers available.

Carbon¨ enables companies to craft what the world needs by combining innovations in software, hardware, and materials to deliver breakthrough products that improve human well-being, transform industries, and change the world.
THE COMPANY WAS FOUNDED IN 2013 AND LAUNCHED ON THE TED STAGE IN 2015, where Co-Founder and Executive Chairman, Dr. Joseph DeSimone, unveiled the scientific breakthrough behind Carbon Digital Light Synthesisª (DLSª) technology for the first time.
Carbon DLS technology fuses light and oxygen to rapidly produce polymer products from a pool of resin. By overcoming limitations of conventional 3D printing, DLS makes it possible to digitally produce parts with unmatched quality and surface finish, and at volumes and speeds never before possible. DLS also empowers designers and engineers to create parts using complex geometries that are impossible to produce using traditional manufacturing methods, opening up new product possibilities. As the worldÕs leading digital manufacturing company, Carbon enables some of the most well-known global brands such as adidas, Riddell, Ford, and Johnson & Johnson to create innovative products with 3D printing technology.
Carbon has customers in 14 countries and is continuing to expand globally in Europe and Asia. The company has more than 500 employees globally and is growing rapidly.
